uth Asian Handball Federation]]. [[Handball]] was founded in India by Choudhary [[Jagat Singh Lohan]] a [[Jat]] from [[Rohtak]] ([[Haryana]]) who was an alumnus of [[YMCA College of Physical Education]] of [[Madras]] (now [[Chennai]]). He was also the first Secretary General of HFI.<ref name=IHF>{{cite web |title=List of Federations:Handball Federation of India |url=http://www.ihf.info/TheIHF/ContinentalFederations/AsianHandballFederationAHF/ListofFederations/HandballFederationofIndia/tabid/4476/Default.aspx |date= |publisher= [[International Handball Federation]] |accessdate=Jan 30, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Member Federations 2009-2012 |url=http://www.asianhandball.org/index.php?option=com_contact&view=categorylist&layout=federation&id=12&Itemid=103&lang=en |date= |publisher= [[Asian Handball Federation]] (AHF)|accessdate=Jan 30, 2013}}</ref> In 2010, the federation elections were held under observers from the Sports Ministry as it had given prior intimation to the ministry about its [[Annual general meeting]] (AGM) and subsequent elections, this created a precedent for other sports federations in the country.<ref>{{cite news |title=Sport Ministry appoints observer for BAI election |url=http://zeenews.india.com/news/others/sport-ministry-appoints-observer-for-bai-election_632501.html |publisher=Zee News |date= June 8, 2010 |accessdate=Jan 30, 2013}}</ref> Since 22 December 2013, Dr. M. Ramasubramani and Dr. Anandeshwar Pandey are President and Secretary General of HFI respectively.\n\n==Formation==\nIn [[India]], sport of [[handball]] and HFI was founded by [[Jagat Singh Lohan]] a [[Jat]] from [[Rohtak]] ([[Haryana]]) who was an alumnus of [[YMCA College of Physical Education]] of [[Madras]] (now [[Chennai]]). He was the also the first Secretary General of HFI. [[Jagat Singh Lohan|Lohan]] was founder/father of [[handball]], [[netball]] and [[throwball]] games in India. His efforts in [[Germany]] during the [[Munich Olympics]] in 1972 helped in establishing HFI. The founding member states were [[Andhra Pradesh]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[Haryana]], [[Vidharbha]] and [[Jammu and Kashmir]]. The '''1st Senior National Handball Championship''' was held at [[Chhotu Ram|Sir Chhotu Ram]] Stadium, [[Rohtak]] ([[Haryana]]) in the year 1972. '''[[Haryana]]''' won the Gold Medal and Vidharba got the silver medal. \nIn India, [[handball]] is currently played at local level in India but hasn't made it big in domestic level. India has yet to make an impact at international level, world championship and the olympic games.\n\n==HFI Presidents==\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#efefef\" align=\"center\" \n!S.No. !! Name !! State !! Tenure\n|-\n|1. ||Mrs. [[Laxmi Chhabla]] || ||\n|-\n|2. ||[[Air Vice Marshal]] [[H. L. Kapur]], [[PVSM]] [[AVSM]] [[Member of parliament, Rajya Sabha|MP]] || [[Uttar Pradesh]] ||\n|-\n|3. ||Dr. [[Roshan Lal Anand]] || [[Delhi]] || 29 November 2005 - 1 February 2010\n|-\n|4. ||Dr. [[Sarwan Singh Channy]], IAS || [[Punjab]] || 1 February 2010 - 22 December 2013\n|-\n|5. ||Dr. [[M. Ramasubramani]], IPS || [[Tamil Nadu]] || 22 December 2013 - Till Date\n|}\n\n==HFI Secretary Generals==\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#efefef\" align=\"center\" \n!S.No. !! Name !! State !! Tenure\n|-\n|1. || Choudhary [[Jagat Singh Lohan]] || [[Rohtak]] ([[Haryana]]) ||1972-1973\n|-\n|2. || Jenab [[M. L. Khan]] || [[Andhra Pradesh]] ||1973-1985\n|-\n|3. || Dr. [[Surinder Mohan Bali]] || [[Jammu]] ([[Jammu and Kashmir]]) ||1985 - December 2013\n|-\n|4. || Dr. [[Anandeshwar Panday]] || [[Lucknow]] ([[Uttar Pradesh]]) || 22 December 2013 - Till Date\n|}\n\n==Structure==\nHandball Federation of India has a well organised structure elected by democratic way i.e., elections.\n\n===HFI Executive Committee===\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#efefef\" align=\"center\" \n! Designation !! Name !! State\n|-\n| '''President''' || Dr. [[M. Ra